DAMATURU – As part of his Ramadan fasting month succour, Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni today were given some palliative in form of cash as a way of supporting the needs of Labourers in Damaturu. The payment and disbursement was performed by Babagana Alhaji Modu Bature Goniri and Alhaji Hassan Shettima. According to reports, more than 50,000 different associations members benefitted from this philanthropic act. One of the beneficiaries who gave his name Malam Abdullahi thanked Governor Mai Mala Buni for the support “we are indeed grateful for this gesture in the holy month of fasting, each of us received the sum of N20, 000 this will go a long way in alleviating our sufferings”. He further commended Governor Buni’s delegation for the fairness “they represented his adequately, they have been very open and transparent in the sharing, we were given irrespective of any difference, we pray God to reward him abundantly.”